surf_ny_arena_v666

This is an update of the original surf_ny_arena. It has a slightly changed system, with surf sections which have been altered in minor ways. The arena is all new, in the same theme.

The new system:
-----------------
- Each level of surf will grant you a better position/weapon in the arena
- Failing to complete any of the 5 levels will put you in a cage in the arena
- There is a 2 minute timer in which you have to complete the surf levels
- You will be awarded a weapon based the the last level you beat before the timer expires
- You may continue to retry levels upon fail or success
- There is a bonus 6th level which can be reached only upon completion of level 5.
- The levels are varying in difficulty, from right to left:
*lvl 1 - gives a knife, fast, safe and easy.
*lvl 2 - gives a pistol; frustrating and a long walk, this is because the level is fairly easy, gives a gun and has no chance to kill the surfer/
*lvl 3 - gives an UMP45, fast, dangerous and easy; this level will kill you if you are not careful/
*lvl 4 - gives an M4A1, low-hp bunny-hopping, dangerous.
*lvl 5 - gives AWP, elevator will take you to this somewhat frustrating level. Upon completion you will be granted access to lvl 6, if you can find it.

The arena will pit the surfers against eachother. It is a dangerous environment. The fail-surfers will be let out of their cage after 30 seconds, there are knives on the floor for them.

Surf_ny_advance
by FAJ
--------------------------------
Skill surf map with 4 phases. The first 3 phases stress a particular skill, with 3 stages. The first stage introduces the skill. the second stage complicates it and the thrid stage adds a gimmick or a more difficult section. The fourth phase test all 3 skills. I would have had more stages, but I ran out of faces/brushes to do it in.
--------------------------------
Timer is 100 seconds, it reverts back to zero everytime a stage is beaten for the first time. Minimum complete time is ~3 minutes.
--------------------------------
This map is designed for 66 tick. It will work on a higher tick, but the moving parts wont move properly and the levels won't be calibrated the same.
--------------------------------

Author's note: The map is probably too difficult for practical multiplayer/pub situations. It is not meant to be for everyone, although I have heard from many surfers that it is not as hard as it looks. I would prefer not to get comments about it being too hard or too easy, as objective difficulty plagues any skill map anyways.

This is a tier 4/5 linear map that is about 1:20 minutes long. The map has a lot of flat, fast jumps with some vertical sections to break it up. The main character of the surf is a lot of fast, acrobatics sections with many turns and smooth ramp entrances. The central mechanic of the map is using landmark teleports to increase your speed in a section in order to progress. This also links in with the futuristic theme. 

  There are two bonuses which are about the same difficulty. One of the bonuses is a straight forward surf that uses more conventional challenges. The other bonus plays with the teleport mechanic as a central part of the challenge.

This is the Final version of Network.
Jail is completely revamped.
The scout area was revamped.
A pro section was added (you have to find the 4 spots that break that glass in the end)

The jail is on a 20 second timer that lets you out, until someone finishes the map. When someone finishes the map, it sends everyone to jail, stopping the timer and holding the ones who didn't make it.
Their are 3 choices of what you can do with the prisoners.
The PRO section gives you 5 chances, for Terrorist and Counter-Terrorist. If there is 2 Cts and 1 T in pro, there is a better chance of the t winning since the 5 fall limit stands for each team.

The rest is for you to find out. Enjoy
-Ryan

Surf_Mystic_beta

Hi all! This is my first submission here in FPSBANANA and my first surf map so... I hope you like it.

Please test it and report any bug you see or any suggestion to improve it.

If you dont know how to test it without a server then follow this instructions :

Firts go to steam->games tab
Then select CSS->right-click it->properties->set launch options->add the following line :

-tickrate 66

(If you have any option already for example "-console" then it would be "-console -tickrate 66")

Now open CSS->Create Server->Select the map->When it launches open up console and type in "sv_airaccelerate 150" without the "s


Your done, now just surf it ;D
